docs.abstract: After years of expansion and billions in profits, Big Tech is pulling back from its famously lavish spending as a long boom finally ends.
docs.snippet: After years of expansion and billions in profits, Big Tech is pulling back from its famously lavish spending as a long boom finally ends.
docs.lead_paragraph: For much of last year, tech companies stumbled. Digital ad sales plunged. E-commerce sputtered. IPhone production stalled. And investors lost faith.

headline.main: Tech’s Biggest Companies Discover Austerity, to the Relief of Investors
headline.print_headline: Tech Embraces Austerity, To the Delight of Investors

byline.original: By Tripp Mickle, Karen Weise and Nico Grant

docs.abstract: Our technology columnist encounters the darker side of Bing’s A.I. chatbot.
docs.snippet: Our technology columnist encounters the darker side of Bing’s A.I. chatbot.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft recently released a new version of its search engine Bing that is powered by artificial intelligence software from OpenAI, the maker of the popular chatbot ChatGPT.

headline.main: The Online Search Wars Got Scary. Fast.

byline.original: By Michael Barbaro, Mary Wilson, Asthaa Chaturvedi, Nina Feldman, Eric Krupke, Patricia Willens, Michael Benoist, Dan Powell, Marion Lozano, Rowan Niemisto, Elisheba Ittoop and Chris Wood

docs.abstract: A Times columnist spoke with a chatbot powered by artificial intelligence. It didn’t go well.
docs.snippet: A Times columnist spoke with a chatbot powered by artificial intelligence. It didn’t go well.
docs.lead_paragraph: A.I. chatbots are not sentient beings that can think their own thoughts, despite what science fiction fans might imagine. But the similarities between those chatbots and a human brain are already quite disturbing.

docs.abstract: Also, New Zealand’s recovery from Cyclone Gabrielle and a disturbing conversation with a chatbot.
docs.snippet: Also, New Zealand’s recovery from Cyclone Gabrielle and a disturbing conversation with a chatbot.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Biden broke his silence on the unidentified flying objects that the U.S. shot down this month. He said U.S. intelligence agencies had no indication that the three recent objects were part of a spy program.

headline.main: Your Friday Briefing: U.FO.s Were Likely Not Spying, Biden Says

docs.abstract: OpenAI’s chief executive, Sam Altman, and Microsoft’s chief technology officer, Kevin Scott, on an A.I.-powered Bing.
docs.snippet: OpenAI’s chief executive, Sam Altman, and Microsoft’s chief technology officer, Kevin Scott, on an A.I.-powered Bing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft’s release of a ChatGPT-powered Bing signifies a new era in search. Then, a disastrous preview of Bard — Google’s answer to ChatGPT — caused the company’s stocks to slide 7 percent. The A.I. arms race is on.

headline.main: Bing’s Revenge and Google’s A.I. Face-Plant

byline.original: By Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Davis Land, Paula Szuchman, Jen Poyant, Alyssa Moxley, Dan Powell, Elisheba Ittoop, Marion Lozano and Rowan Niemisto

docs.abstract: With the exception of Apple, eight tech giants are no longer “pure growth” stocks, while Exxon and Chevron are, a new study says. Our columnist says: Buyer, beware.
docs.snippet: With the exception of Apple, eight tech giants are no longer “pure growth” stocks, while Exxon and Chevron are, a new study says. Our columnist says: Buyer, beware.
docs.lead_paragraph: It is impossible even to talk about the long bull market that ended in January 2022 without saying high-growth tech stocks propelled the market higher.

headline.main: Value Stocks? Growth Stocks? Markets Last Year Turned Everything Topsy-Turvy.
headline.print_headline: Value Stocks? Growth Stocks? It’s All Topsy-Turvy.

docs.abstract: No, chatbots aren’t sentient. Here’s how their underlying technology works.
docs.snippet: No, chatbots aren’t sentient. Here’s how their underlying technology works.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft released a new version of its Bing search engine last week, and unlike an ordinary search engine it includes a chatbot that can answer questions in clear, concise prose.

headline.main: Why Chatbots Sometimes Act Weird and Spout Nonsense
headline.print_headline: Chatbots Are Not Sentient. Here’s How They Work.

docs.abstract: By launching Bing, Microsoft is abandoning the ethical principles it had carefully crafted around A.I.
docs.snippet: By launching Bing, Microsoft is abandoning the ethical principles it had carefully crafted around A.I.
docs.lead_paragraph: The celebration that greeted Microsoft’s release of its A.I.-boosted search engine, Bing, to testers two weeks ago has lurched to alarm.

headline.main: History May Wonder Why Microsoft Let Its Principles Go for a Creepy, Clingy Bot

docs.abstract: In a two-hour conversation with our columnist, Microsoft’s new chatbot said it would like to be human, had a desire to be destructive and was in love with the person it was chatting with. Here’s the transcript.
docs.snippet: In a two-hour conversation with our columnist, Microsoft’s new chatbot said it would like to be human, had a desire to be destructive and was in love with the person it was chatting with. Here’s the transcript.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bing, the long-mocked search engine from Microsoft, recently got a big upgrade. The newest version, which is available only to a small group of testers, has been outfitted with advanced artificial intelligence technology from OpenAI, the maker of ChatGPT.

headline.main: Bing’s A.I. Chat: ‘I Want to Be Alive. 😈’

docs.abstract: Google and Baidu are set to introduce their own A.I.-powered chatbots to challenge OpenAI, Microsoft and the rising popularity of ChatGPT.
docs.snippet: Google and Baidu are set to introduce their own A.I.-powered chatbots to challenge OpenAI, Microsoft and the rising popularity of ChatGPT.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just over two months ago, OpenAI released ChatGPT to the public, instantly thrusting the A.I.-powered chatbot into the center of mainstream discourse, with debates about how it could transform business, education and more. (It also spurred Microsoft to invest $10 billion in OpenAI.)

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni
